summary: In this context, 1,1,2-trichloroethene (TCE) is discussed in relation to bioremediation efforts at a contaminated site, focusing on microbial activity and the treatment of TCE. However, there is no mention or exploration of any relationship between TCE and age-related macular degeneration (AMD). The two terms appear in the same context but are not connected in terms of biological or chemical relevance.
